Program: Outlook
Title: 07/07/2009
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p003jjp6
Last Broadcast Date: Tue 7 Jul 2009
Personal stories behind the news from all over the world. With Jonathan Charles. On today's programme: In Guantanamo at 14; J8 not G8; and skyward glamour. Guantanamo Bay's youngest inmate? Mohammed El Gharani on his new life in Chad after seven years in Guantanamo. J8 What would you say to Barack Obama and the other G8 leaders if you were invited to their summit in Italy, this week? 16 year old Emanuella Louisdor, from Florida, is among a group of youngsters getting just that opportunity. Glamour in the skies Libbie Escolme-Schmidt describes what it was like to be a stewardess during the golden age of air travel. Show less